{"type":"FeatureCollection","features":[{"type":"Feature","geometry":{"type":"GeometryCollection","geometries":[{"type":"Point","coordinates":[144.80390593911488,-37.83138610861039]},{"type":"Polygon","coordinates":[[[144.79785487557882,-37.82125139588904],[144.81339023018668,-37.82213279104322],[144.81424853707733,-37.84152082133174],[144.7935633411524,-37.8408430041319],[144.79785487557882,-37.82125139588904]]]}]},"properties":{"feedType":"warning","cap":{"category":"CBRNE","event":"Chemical Hazard","eventCode":"chemical","urgency":"Unknown","severity":"Unknown","certainty":"Observed","contact":"george.skoufezis@justice.vic.gov.au","senderName":"Fire Rescue Victoria","responseType":"None"},"sourceOrg":"EMV","sourceId":"41949","sourceFeed":"cop-cap","sourceTitle":"Community Information","id":"41949","category1":"Community Update","category2":"CBRNE","status":"Unknown","name":"Community Information","action":"Stay Informed","statewide":"N","location":"Altona North, Laverton North","created":"2026-05-18T17:18:50+10:00","updated":"2026-05-18T17:18:51+10:00","webHeadline":null,"webBody":"<div style=\"margin-bottom:20px\">This <b>message </b>is being issued for <span title=\"warning_locality\" class=\"param\" contenteditable=\"false\">Altona North, Laverton North</span>.<div><ul><li>There\nis a hazardous liquid leak in Pipe Road, Laverton North. </li><li>The incident is contained.</li><li>This Community Information replaces the Advice issued at 8:26am, Monday 18 May.</li></ul></div></div><div style=\"font-size: 120%; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom:20px\">There is no immediate threat to the community and no action is required. </div><div style=\"margin-bottom:20px\">This message was issued\nby <span title=\"warning_issuing_agency\" class=\"param\" contenteditable=\"false\">Fire Rescue Victoria</span>.&nbsp;<div><br></div><div><b>Unless the situation changes this will be the last message for this incident.</b></div><div><br></div><div><b>Use multiple sources to stay informed: </b></div><div><ul><li><a href=\"http://emergency.vic.gov.au/respond/\" title=\"www.emergency.vic.gov.au\" target=\"_blank\">www.emergency.vic.gov.au</a>.</li><li><a href=\"https://vicemergency.zendesk.com/hc/en-gb/articles/115001055007-What-is-the-VicEmergency-Hotline-\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">VicEmergency Hotline</a> - freecall 1800 226 226.</li><li><a href=\"https://vicemergency.zendesk.com/hc/en-gb/articles/230492607-What-is-the-VicEmergency-app-\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: white;\">VicEmergency app</a>.</li><li><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/vicemergency\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\"> Facebook</a> or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/vicemergency\" title=\"Twitter\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: white;\">Twitter</a>&nbsp;(#vichazmat).</li><li>Tune in to ABC Local Radio, commercial and designated community radio stations, or Sky News TV. </li></ul><div><b>Accessibility:&nbsp;</b></div></div><div>The following services can\nhelp you, or someone you know, access information during an emergency.&nbsp;</div><div><ul><li>To access this information\n     in other languages, call the <a href=\"https://www.tisnational.gov.au/\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">Translating and Interpreting Service</a>&nbsp;on&nbsp;131 450&nbsp;(freecall) and ask\n     them to call VicEmergency Hotline. &nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>If you are deaf, hard of\nhearing, or have a speech/communication impairment contact the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.infrastructure.gov.au/media-communications-arts/phone/services-people-disability/accesshub/national-relay-service\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">National Relay Service</a>&nbsp;and ask them to call the\nVicEmergency Hotline. </li></ul></div></div>","text":"COMMUNITY INFORMATION - CHEMICAL HAZARD - Stay Informed\nIncident Location: Pipe Road, Laverton North\nIssue Date: Monday 18 May 2026, 05:18 pm\nNext Update: Tuesday 19 May 2026, 01:00 pm\n\nMore details at http://emergency.vic.gov.au/respond/#!/